cs.AR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses an optimization to improve the memory usage of RNNs, which falls under the category of architecture optimization. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on measuring the scheduling efficiency of RNNs for NLP applications, which falls under the category of computation and language. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): RNNs are a type of machine learning model, and the paper discusses an optimization to improve their efficiency, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper focuses on NLP applications, RNNs are also commonly used in computer vision applications such as image captioning, which falls under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the impact of RNN scheduling on energy efficiency, which falls under the category of systems and control.
